cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with device-to-device (D2D) communication and optimization of content pushing strategy to maximize offloading gain. The paper focuses on the participation of human users, their content preferences, and sharing willingness. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization problems, which can fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also deals with content sharing, which can be related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
